      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk, that feels like such a cop-out answer lol. i mean, looking at the actual text and the historical records from that era, isn't it pretty clear what they were thinking? like, if you look at the originalist perspective, it's based on actual history and docs, whereas the other side just seems to be making up new meanings as they go along to fit modern vibes. don't you think the originalist approach is more grounded in actual law?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
